devdoc.details: This contract handles deposits to and withdrawals from the liquidity pools that power RariFund as well as currency exchanges via 0x.

_getPoolBalance(uint8).details: Returns the fund controller's balance of the specified currency in the specified pool.Ideally, we can add the view modifier, but Compound's `getUnderlyingBalance` function (called by `CompoundPoolController.getBalance`) potentially modifies the state.

_upgradeFundController(address).details: Sets or upgrades RariFundController by forwarding immediate balance of ETH from the old to the new.

params.newContract: The address of the new RariFundController contract.

approveCompTo0x(uint256).details: Approves tokens to 0x without spending gas on every deposit.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be approved.

approveWethToDydxPool(uint256).details: Approves tokens to the specified pool without spending gas on every deposit.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be approved.

constructor.details: Constructor that sets supported ERC20 token contract addresses and supported pools for each supported token.

depositToPool(uint8,uint256).details: Deposits funds to the specified pool.

disableFund().details: Disables primary functionality of this RariFundController so contract(s) can be upgraded.

enableFund().details: Enables primary functionality of this RariFundController once contract(s) are upgraded.

getEntireBalance().details: Ideally, we can add the view modifier, but Compound's `getUnderlyingBalance` function (called by `getPoolBalance`) potentially modifies the state.
getEntireBalance().return: An array of pool indexes and an array of corresponding balances.

getPoolBalance(uint8).details: Returns the fund controller's balance of the specified currency in the specified pool.Ideally, we can add the view modifier, but Compound's `getUnderlyingBalance` function (called by `CompoundPoolController.getBalance`) potentially modifies the state.

hasETHInPool(uint8).details: Return a boolean indicating if the fund controller has funds in `currencyCode` in `pool`.

params.pool: The index of the pool to check.

initialize(address).details: Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

marketSell0xOrdersFillOrKill((address,ad.details: Market sell to 0x exchange orders (reverting if `takerAssetFillAmount` is not filled). We should be able to make this function external and use calldata for all parameters, but Solidity does not support calldata structs (https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/5479).

params.orders: The limit orders to be filled in ascending order of price.
params.takerAssetFillAmount: The amount of the taker asset to sell (excluding taker fees).

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * > Note: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setAaveReferralCode(uint16).details: Sets the referral code for Aave deposits.

setFundManager(address).details: Sets or upgrades the RariFundManager of the RariFundController.

params.newContract: The address of the new RariFundManager contract.

setFundRebalancer(address).details: Sets or upgrades the rebalancer of the RariFundController.

params.newAddress: The Ethereum address of the new rebalancer server.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeFundController(address).details: Sets or upgrades RariFundController by withdrawing all ETH from all pools and forwarding them from the old to the new.

params.newContract: The address of the new RariFundController contract.

withdrawAllFromPool(uint8).details: Withdraws all funds from the specified pool.

withdrawAllFromPoolOnUpgrade(uint8).details: Withdraws all funds from the specified pool (without requiring the fund to be enabled).

withdrawFromPool(uint8,uint256).details: Withdraws funds from the specified pool.

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be withdrawn.

withdrawFromPoolKnowingBalance(uint8,uin.details: Withdraws funds from the specified pool (caching the `initialBalance` parameter).

params.amount: The amount of tokens to be withdrawn.
params.initialBalance: The fund's balance of the specified currency in the specified pool before the withdrawal.

withdrawFromPoolKnowingBalanceToManager(.details: Withdraws funds from the specified pool and sends it to RariFundManager (caching the `initialBalance` parameter).

params.amount: The amount of ETH to be withdrawn.
params.initialBalance: The fund's balance of the specified currency in the specified pool before the withdrawal.

withdrawToManager(uint256).details: Withdraws ETH and sends amount to the manager.

devdoc.title: RariFundController

getEntireBalance().notice: Returns the fund controller's balance of each pool of the specified currency.
